h.gov/10222516/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Semin+Ultrasound+CT+MR&amp;publication_year=1999&amp;pages=77&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS0887-2171%2899%2990039-2&amp;pmid=10222516">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/28/2" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2008.28.issue-2/asset/14a1685b-ce14-1685-ace1-a1685bace14a/radiographics.2008.28.issue-2.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">28</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2008</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">393</span> - <span property="pageEnd">405</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18349447/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18349447</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2008.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2008</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.282075039">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keyword</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPR+%3D+multiplanar+reformation&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPR = multiplanar reformation</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">CT appearances of the normal appendix and the typical features of appendicitis are discussed and illustrated, as well as some of the difficulties in diagnosing appendicitis at conventional CT and the role of multiplanar reformation in overcoming them.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-a